    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <para>Place auxiliary drive gear, retainer and 15/16 bolt on the output shaft assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13019g5">Figure 165</hotlnk>). Secure the bolt on the shaft until tight. Recommended torque
            will be applied during final assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f13019g5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13019g5" filename="../figg13/g13019g5.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 165. Place Auxiliary Drive Gear, Retainer and Bolt on Output Shaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
